      • addApplicantMessage

        public void addApplicantMessage​(User applicant,
                                String message)
                         throws IllegalStateException
        Add/modify applicant message in the enquiry if the enquiry is not solved.
        Parameters:
        applicant - The applicant who is sending the message.
        message - The message content.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the enquiry is already solved, or if there was an error updating the enquiry in the database.

      • addReplyMessage

        public void addReplyMessage​(User user,
                            String message)
                     throws IllegalStateException
        Add reply message in the enquiry if the enquiry is not solved, and set the enquiry as solved.
        Parameters:
        user - The user who is replying to the enquiry.
        message - The reply message content.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the enquiry is already solved.

      • deleteEnquiry

        public void deleteEnquiry()
                   throws IllegalStateException
        Delete the enquiry by marking it as solved.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if there was an error updating the enquiry in the database.
